Class SortingAlgorithmBenchmark

java.lang.Object
SortingAlgorithmBenchmark
public class SortingAlgorithmBenchmark extends Object
A class to benchmark various sorting algorithms on medical records datasets.

This class provides functionality to read datasets from CSV files, sort the datasets using different sorting algorithms, and measure the performance of these algorithms.

It supports three different datasets: ascending order, descending order, and random order. The class benchmarks Bubble Sort, Insertion Sort, and Selection Sort algorithms, and records the number of statements executed by each algorithm.

The class uses multithreading to read the datasets concurrently and utilizes an ExecutorService to perform sorting operations in parallel.

  • Method Details

    • readData

      protected static void readData(int choice)
      Reads data from CSV files and populates arrays of MedicalRecords objects.

      This method initializes the arrays for medical records and starts separate threads to read data from CSV files concurrently. After reading, it waits for all threads to finish before returning.

      Parameters:
      choice - an integer representing the size of the dataset to be used. It corresponds to the index in the DATASET_SIZES array (1-based index).

    • readMedicalRecordsFromCSV

      public static void readMedicalRecordsFromCSV(String fileName, MedicalRecords[] medicalRecordsArray)
      Reads medical records from a CSV file and populates the provided array.

      This method processes the CSV file line by line, parsing the fields and creating MedicalRecords objects. It handles cases where medications may contain commas and provides appropriate error messages if the file is not found or if there is an issue reading the file.

      Parameters:
      fileName - the path to the CSV file.
      medicalRecordsArray - the array to populate with MedicalRecords objects.

    • sortData

      protected static void sortData()
      Sorts the medical records data using various sorting algorithms and measures the performance.

      This method creates tasks for sorting the data using Bubble Sort, Insertion Sort, and Selection Sort algorithms. It submits these tasks to an ExecutorService to be executed in parallel and collects the results. The number of statements executed by each sorting algorithm is recorded in the static arrays BUBBLE_SORT_RESULTS, INSERTION_SORT_RESULTS, and SELECTION_SORT_RESULTS.
